A MODERN fish market built at 1.5bn/- in Bagamoyo District, Coast Region is expected bring major economic transformation to the council and residents in the area. District Executive Director (DED) Mr Shauri Selenda said in Bagamoyo Town recently that   the market became operational this month, after completion of five buildings out of seven. “We started using this market from July 1 this year but it will be fully operational comes   July 31, this year. According to Mr Selenda, the second phase of the project will include construction of shops and food vendors' rooms. He said, "we are waiting for the government to releases fund so that we can start the second phase implementation of this project". Mr Selenda further said that, several committees have been formed to ensure that the market and its infrastructure are protected and remains in good condition. “This project means a lot to us... majority of residents depend on fishing for living. Our district is also well known as historical town and receives a large number of tourists each year.  This kind of market will be another tourists site," he said. Mr Selenda expressed gratitude to President SamiaSuluhu Hassan for dishing out fund   for the project pledging to make close monitoring of the project.